Chatsworth Police are appealing for witnesses to assist in a murder case that is being investigated after a man was shot and succumbed to his injuries at the Everest Shopping Centre in Shallcross on Monday, 7 February. Communications Officer of the Chatsworth SAPS, Captain Cheryl Pillay, said the 36-year-old African male succumbed to his injuries following the fatal shooting. Anyone with information can contact the investigating officer, Detective Sergeant Sosibo, at Chatsworth SAPS on 031-451-4314 or alternatively call at Room DLG4. Police guarantee anonymity to witnesses who can assist in this investigation.